  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sleep after surgery has been found to be very distrubed immediately after major surgery. This
      is also seen after fast-track hip and knee replacement with length of stay of less than 3
      days. Disturbed sleep has many adverse effects i.e. fatigue, possible hyperalgesia and
      decline in cognitive abilities.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
